ritize P1/P2 evidence: BTC leader behavior and shadow reject quality are the tie-breakers.\n\n## 2026-05-03 00:48 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] HL telemetry now exposes execution_mode directly\n\n**Task:** Add a first-class HL execution mode to live telemetry so dashboard/monitoring can distinguish funded monitor mode from fully tradeable mode without inferring from multiple fields.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- Prior HL telemetry exposed the raw ingredients: `wallet_blocked=false`, `order_notional_blocked=true`, `planned_order_notional=11.217492`, `min_order_notional_usd=20.0`.\n- But `status` was still generically `live`, which could be misread as live-tradeable.\n- I patched `/home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py` so `write_live_state()` now computes execution modes:\n  - `wallet_blocked` when balance is below `$10`\n  - `notional_blocked` when wallet is funded but planned order notional is below `$20`\n  - `live_tradeable` when both gates pass\n- The payload now includes ",
